{"key":"post-13630541","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13630541</id>\n<content>It's not just about the rice flour.&amp;nbsp; BRF cakes are 2/3 vermiculite, which is mineral.&amp;nbsp; In addition, I've been doing a lot of experimenting with gypsum lately, since I prepare nearly 1,000 pounds of substrates per week.&amp;nbsp; You can reduce gypsum to 2% to 3% by volume and not see a reduction in performance with most substrates.&amp;nbsp; When I first started recommending gypsum several years ago, I was using ten percent and got much improved results over not using it at all.&amp;nbsp; However, now I have found you can reduce that amount quite a bit and still get the same results.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13635055</next>\n<prev>13629636</prev>\n<first>13629455</first>\n<last>13635055</last>\n<when>1292341938</when>\n<utime>12/14/10 05:52 PM</utime>\n</post>"}